The paper deals with the problem of incomplete data in computer vision, specifically occluded objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a framework for augmenting recurrent processing capabilities into a feedforward network, which involves modifying hidden layer activity and propagating to lower layers. This suggests that the paper is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper uses a mixture model and generates samples of the last hidden layer, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with classification, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
